  "title": "10x Chromium 3\u2032 GEX v3",
  "description": "A droplet-based single-cell 3\u2032 gene expression assay. Cells are co-partitioned with barcoded gel beads into nanoliter Gel-Beads-in-emulsion (GEMs); inside each GEM, poly(dT) primers bearing a 16 bp 10x cell barcode and 12 bp UMI reverse-transcribe polyadenylated mRNA into barcoded full-length cDNA via template switching. Pooled cDNA is amplified, fragmented, and built into standard Illumina paired-end libraries. Read 1 sequences the 16 bp barcode + 12 bp UMI, the i7 index read gives the sample index, and Read 2 sequences the 3\u2032 cDNA insert, yielding digital 3\u2032 transcript counts per single cell.",
